    <div class="section" id="p1">
        <span class="name">Hon. IBRAHIM, Funsho Ganiyu, M.Sc. (Leeds) FCA, (Chairman)</span>
        <span class="border"></span>
        <p>
            Born on 18th February 1955, Mallam F.G. Ibrahim is a multi-disciplinary technocrat whose experiences in various facets of Nigeria Private and public Sectors span over three decades. After graduating in Accountancy from The Polytechnic Ibadan in 1982, he started his banking career with Afribank in 1983. A fellow of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of Nigeria (ICAN) and Nigeria Institute of Management, he qualified as a Chartered Accountant in May, 1986. He also holds a Master of Science Degree in Corporate Governance from the LEEDS METROPOLITAN UNIVERSITY, UK.
        </p>
        <p>He left Afribank after 6 years to set up and pioneer, the Corporate Finance Department of Trade Bank Plc in March 1989, as a Manager. He held various management positions in the bank in the areas including retail, corporate, investment and development banking. He  was later elevated to the Board of the bank, as an Executive Director, Finance and Management Services in 1998, the position he held until he retired voluntarily from the Board of the Bank into private business in 2002.  </p>
        <p>An Alumnus of the prestigious Lagos Business School (LBS), Mallam Ibrahim attended many courses locally and overseas as part of his management development programmes in the areas of capital market operations and investment banking. His business interests include Engineering Construction, Agriculture, Mining, Financial Consultancy. He had Federal appointments as the Chairman, Board of Directors, Centre for Black and African Arts and Civilization (CBAAC), Director, Abuja Investments Ltd. and member, Financial Thematic Group, VISION 20 2020. </p>
        <p>
            He also served for three years as an elected Chairman, Yagba East Local Government Council, Kogi State (2013-2016).
            He is currently the Chairman, Governing Council, Federal College of Education (Techical) Asaba.
            He is happily married with children.
        </p>
    </div>
