    <div class="section" id="p5">
        <span class="name">Engr. Olawale K. Okunade MNSE (Executive Director / CEO)</span>
        <span class="border"></span>
        <p>
            Engr. Okunade graduated from University of Ibadan where he had a B.Sc. Degree in Engineering
            and a Master’s Degree in Engineering from the same University in view. In addition, he holds
            postgraduate qualifications in Finance & Credit Management and Advanced Certificate in
            Network Computing/Information Technology alongside professional qualifications in Management,
            Marketing, Public Relations and Pensions Management. He is a result-oriented and highly
            resourceful manager who has traversed management profession in areas including Strategic
            Planning, Corporate Management, Project Management/Financing, Mortgages, Micro-Finance,
            Investment and Financial Management, Business Development, Corporate Communications,
            Relationship Management, Systems Re-engineering, Performance Evaluation & Management,
            Valuation/Cost Management, Capacity Building and Knowledge Management.
        </p>
        <p>
            Prior to forming CATED, he held key management positions at various times in the following
            capacities; GM/CEO, Afriprops Development Company Ltd, General Manager/CEO, Engineering
            Practice Resource Development, EPRD a Training & Engineering Consulting firm owned by the
            Nigerian Society of Engineers, General Manager/CEO REDAN Capital Ltd, a housing finance,
            mortgages, leasing, project management & consulting company owned by the Real Estate
            Developers Association of Nigeria, REDAN, where he was dealing with with international
            organizations like Shelter Afrique, L'Agence Française de Développement, Nerida
            International, USA.
        </p>
        <p>
            Engr. Okunade was also at various times Regional Manager, Regency Assets Management Ltd, Branch Manager, Profund Securities Ltd, Branch Manager, the then Intercontinental Homes Savings & Loans Ltd, Senior Manager, Wealthways Leasing and Consulting, Manager, LESAM Global Concept Ltd, Senior Banking Officer, Gateway Bank Plc. He also taught Engineering in Lagos State Polytechnic.
        </p>
        <p>
            He served as Member of the following National Committees; 1st National Urban Forum in Nigeria on Housing and Sustainable Urban Development (UN Habitat III), National Committee for Review of National Housing and Urban Development Policies, Member National Housing Committee of the Federal Ministry of Lands, Housing and Urban Development/UN-Habitat, Member, Nigeria Building & Road Research Institute (NBRRI)/REDAN Joint Committee on the Development of Affordable Mass Housing in Nigeria, Member, Reviewing Committee for National Housing and Urban Development Policies for Federal Ministry of Lands, Housing and Urban Development.
        </p>
        <p>
            He is a Member of the Nigerian Society of Engineers, Nigerian Institution of Agricultural Engineers, Institute of Credit Administration Nigeria, National Institute of Marketing of Nigeria, Nigerian Institute of Management, Nigeria Institute of Public Relations, Certified Pensions Institute of Nigeria and Institute of Internal Auditors. He is a Fellow of both the Environmental Practitioners’ Institute of Nigeria (EPIN) and the Centre for Housing and Infrastructure Finance In Africa, (CHIFIA) a Pan- African Housing Finance and Capacity development Institution based in Nigeria.
        </p>
